KEYMAPOPTS="us us"
HOSTNAMEOPTS="-n alpine-docker"
INTERFACESOPTS="auto"
TIMEZONEOPTS="-z UTC"
PROXYOPTS="none"
APKREPOSOPTS="http://dl-cdn.alpinelinux.org/alpine/v3.20/main
http://dl-cdn.alpinelinux.org/alpine/v3.20/community"
SSHDOPTS="-c openssh"
NTPOPTS="-c busybox"
DISKOPTS="-m sys /dev/vda"
ROOT_PASSWORD="dockerintermux"
USEROPTS="-a -u docker -G wheel -s /bin/ash -f 'Docker User'"
USER_PASSWORD="docker"
```
**Explanation and improvements:**
- Sets a US keyboard layout.
- Sets a descriptive hostname.
- Configures network interfaces to auto.
- Sets timezone to UTC (change if you prefer).
- No proxy.
- Uses the latest Alpine v3.20 main and community repositories.
- Installs and configures OpenSSH and NTP (busybox).
- Installs to `/dev/vda` with sys mode (adjust if needed, e.g., `/dev/sda` depending on detected disk).
- Sets a root password (`dockerintermux`) and creates a `docker` user with password `docker`, part of the `wheel` group for `sudo` access.
- All settings are non-interactive and speed up the install process.
- **You may change the passwords!**

If your VM uses a different disk device (e.g., `vda` vs `sda`), adjust the `DISKOPTS` accordingly!
